raw_text: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM fact.FACT_SALES
SELECT CustomerID, CustomerName, Email FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER WHERE CustomerID = 12345
SELECT ProductID, ProductName, Category, Price FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT WHERE Category = 'Electronics'
SELECT ProductID, ProductName FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT WHERE ProductName LIKE '%Laptop%'
SELECT SaleID, CustomerID, ProductID, Quantity, TotalAmount FROM fact.FACT_SALES WHERE CustomerID = 12345
SELECT ProductID, SUM(Quantity) as TotalQuantity, SUM(TotalAmount) as TotalRevenue FROM fact.FACT_SALES GROUP BY ProductID
SELECT c.CustomerID, c.CustomerName, s.SaleID, s.TotalAmount FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER c INNER JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON c.CustomerID = s.CustomerID
SELECT p.ProductID, p.ProductName, s.SaleID, s.Quantity, s.TotalAmount FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT p INNER JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON p.ProductID = s.ProductID
SELECT SaleDate, SUM(TotalAmount) as DailyRevenue FROM fact.FACT_SALES GROUP BY SaleDate ORDER BY SaleDate
SELECT * FROM fact.FACT_SALES WHERE SaleDate BETWEEN '2024-01-01' AND '2024-12-31'
SELECT TOP 10 ProductID, SUM(TotalAmount) as Revenue FROM fact.FACT_SALES GROUP BY ProductID ORDER BY Revenue DESC

SELECT c.CustomerName, COUNT(s.SaleID) as OrderCount, SUM(s.TotalAmount) as TotalSpent FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER c LEFT JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON c.CustomerID = s.CustomerID GROUP BY c.CustomerID, c.CustomerName
SELECT AVG(TotalAmount) as AvgSale, MIN(TotalAmount) as MinSale, MAX(TotalAmount) as MaxSale FROM fact.FACT_SALES
SELECT p.Category, COUNT(DISTINCT s.CustomerID) as UniqueCustomers FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT p INNER JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON p.ProductID = s.ProductID GROUP BY p.Category
SELECT CustomerID, COUNT(*) as PurchaseCount FROM fact.FACT_SALES GROUP BY CustomerID HAVING COUNT(*) > 5
SELECT YEAR(SaleDate) as Year, MONTH(SaleDate) as Month, SUM(TotalAmount) as MonthlyRevenue FROM fact.FACT_SALES GROUP BY YEAR(SaleDate), MONTH(SaleDate) ORDER BY Year, Month
SELECT c.CustomerID, c.CustomerName, c.City FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER c WHERE c.City IN ('New York', 'Los Angeles', 'Chicago')
SELECT p.ProductID, p.ProductName, p.Price FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT p WHERE p.Price BETWEEN 100 AND 500 ORDER BY p.Price

SELECT c.CustomerID, c.CustomerName, p.ProductName, s.TotalAmount FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER c INNER JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON c.CustomerID = s.CustomerID INNER JOIN dim.DIM_PRODUCT p ON s.ProductID = p.ProductID WHERE s.TotalAmount > 1000
SELECT DISTINCT CustomerID FROM fact.FACT_SALES
SELECT ProductID, Quantity FROM fact.FACT_SALES WHERE Quantity > 10 ORDER BY Quantity DESC

SELECT c.CustomerName, SUM(s.TotalAmount) as TotalSpent FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER c INNER JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON c.CustomerID = s.CustomerID WHERE c.City = 'New York' GROUP BY c.CustomerID, c.CustomerName

SELECT p.Category, AVG(s.Quantity) as AvgQuantity, SUM(s.TotalAmount) as CategoryRevenue FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT p INNER JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON p.ProductID = s.ProductID GROUP BY p.Category ORDER BY CategoryRevenue DESC
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ProductID) as UniqueProducts, COUNT(DISTINCT CustomerID) as UniqueCustomers FROM fact.FACT_SALES
SELECT c.Email FROM dim.DIM_CUSTOMER c WHERE c.Email IS NOT NULL
SELECT SaleDate, COUNT(*) as TransactionCount FROM fact.FACT_SALES WHERE SaleDate >= DATEADD(day, -30, GETDATE()) GROUP BY SaleDate ORDER BY SaleDate DESC
SELECT p.ProductID, p.ProductName, ISNULL(SUM(s.Quantity), 0) as TotalSold FROM dim.DIM_PRODUCT p LEFT JOIN fact.FACT_SALES s ON p.ProductID = s.ProductID GROUP BY p.ProductID, p.ProductName
SELECT CustomerID, TotalAmount FROM fact.FACT_SALES WHERE TotalAmount = (SELECT MAX(TotalAmount) FROM fact.FACT_SALES)
